.TH "overlay_fixup_phandle" 9 "overlay_fixup_phandle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
overlay_fixup_phandle \- Set an overlay phandle to the base one
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" overlay_fixup_phandle
.BI "(void *fdt "  ","
.BI "void *fdto "  ","
.BI "int symbols_off "  ","
.BI "int property "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fdt" 12
Base Device Tree blob
.IP "fdto" 12
Device tree overlay blob
.IP "symbols_off" 12
Node offset of the symbols node in the base device tree
.IP "property" 12
Property offset in the overlay holding the list of fixups
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBoverlay_fixup_phandle\fP resolves all the overlay phandles pointed
to in a __fixups__ property, and updates them to match the phandles
in use in the base device tree.

This is part of the device tree overlay application process, when
you want all the phandles in the overlay to point to the actual
base dt nodes.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success
Negative error code on failure
